inspect_utils¶

Functions¶

Description¶

Inspect UI elements for the current interactive Maya session.

msTools.coreUI.maya.inspect_utils.getFullName(obj)¶

Return the full hierarchical name of a Qt object.

This is the name which uniquely identifies the element within Maya and can be passed to Maya’s UI commands.

Parameters:obj (T <= PySide2.QtCore.QObject) – A Qt object.
Returns:str – The full hierarchical name of obj.
msTools.coreUI.maya.inspect_utils.getMainWindow()¶

Return a Qt widget for the main Maya window.

Raises:msTools.coreUI.maya.exceptions.MayaUILookupError – If the main Maya window could not be identified.
Returns:PySide2.QtWidgets.QMainWindow – Widget for the main Maya window.
msTools.coreUI.maya.inspect_utils.getPanelUnderCursor()¶

Return a Qt widget for the Maya panel under the current cursor position.

Raises:msTools.coreUI.maya.exceptions.MayaUILookupError – If there is no Maya panel under the current cursor position.
Returns:PySide2.QtWidgets.QWidget – Widget for the Maya panel under the current cursor position.
msTools.coreUI.maya.inspect_utils.getWidget(widgetName, widgetClass=None)¶

Return a Qt widget identified by name. Implicitly cast to the most suitable class or explicitly cast to a given class.

Parameters:
  • widgetName (basestring) – Name of the widget such as 'myButton' or a hierarchical path to the widget such as 'myWindow|myButton'. If the name corresponds to an element created using Maya commands, the names of any child layouts (placeholder widgets) must be included within the hierarchy.
  • widgetClass (type, optional) – A (non-strict) subclass of PySide2.QtCore.QObject used as the explicit casting type for the underlying Qt widget. Defaults to None - implicitly cast to the most suitable class, guaranteed to be a (non-strict) subclass of PySide2.QtWidgets.QWidget.
Raises:

msTools.coreUI.maya.exceptions.MayaUILookupError – If widgetName does not correspond to an existing Qt widget.
Returns:

T <= PySide2.QtCore.QObject – Widget corresponding to widgetName, with type given by widgetClass or determined implicitly if None.
